    "developed an AR prototype for post-total hip arthroplasty (THA) evaluation, allowing surgeons to interact with 3D representations of the patient's pelvis and femur in real time to assess joint kinematics and locate impingement points [120].",
    "Similarly, Ulrich et al.",
    "demonstrated how AR can enhance osteotomies by offering superior visualization and reducing the cognitive load on surgeons, improving accuracy and operational efficiency [121].",
    "Condino et al.",
    "developed a hybrid simulator for hip arthroplasty using Microsoft HoloLens and patient-specific 3D models, which allowed surgeons to train with high accuracy in component positioning and low cognitive workload [122]."
